description: After surviving a brutal attack in Opal City, the Shade must leave his beloved home in search of answers. His first stop is Hamburg, Germany, where the violent, invulnerable private investigator Von Hammer has the first piece of the puzzle. But to reach the detective, the Shade must duel with darkness against French shadow villain Bete Noir. The menace and mystery are just beginning in this second part of the Shade's global odyssey!
name: Those First Few Steps

description:
Reprint from Smash! comic - two Janus Stark adventures:

  • Cry Vengeance
  • The Body Snatchers
name: Janus Stark

description: Skywolf, Bald Eagle and Baron von Tundra in the bloodiest battle of Viet Nam? Who will survive?
name: Breakout!

description: The superstar team of writer Geoff Johns and artist Jim Lee continue to make history as they unleash the amazing Amazon, Wonder Woman, who joins the battle against a bizarre threat! And the not-yet World’s Greatest Heroes need all the help they can get!
name: Justice League, Part Three

description: The generational crime drama we call "The Icelandic Trilogy," continues! The Hauksson's making inroads into Icelandic politics, swapping one form of intimidation for another. The son of the son of the son of the son of Ulf Hauksson possesses his great-grandfather's frontier brutality, but can he navigate the modern world?
name: The Icelandic Trilogy, Part 5: Christianity 999

description: This issue marks the beginning of a new story arc, "Dead Reckoning." With her comfortable life-after-death thrown into complete disarray and her romantic relationships in shambles, the last thing Gwen wants to do is leave town. But when she eats the brain of an aging hippie, she finds herself compelled to go on the road, to follow the hippie's favorite band on their farewell tour across America.
name: Staying In

description:
Catch up on the Event of the Year!

Discover the series that has everyone buzzing with this introductory priced trade paperback collection released to coincide with the beginning of the second chapter of the yearlong event! Separately, thirteen mystical Artifacts will guide the fate of the Universe. Together, thirteen Artifacts will end the Universe. When a mysterious antagonist kidnaps, Hope, the daughter of Sara Pezzini and Jackie Estacado, Armageddon is put into motion. Starring virtually every character in the Top Cow Universe, this is a series for diehard fans and new readers alike.

Written by Top Cow Universe architect Ron Marz (WITCHBLADE, MAGDALENA) with the art team of Michael Broussard (THE DARKNESS), Rick Basaldua (THE DARKNESS), Sal Regla (MAGDALENA) and Sunny Gho of IFS (VELOCITY), this volume collects ARTIFACTS #1-#4 along with the Free Comic Book Day #0 issue and a beautiful cover gallery, behind-the-scenes extras, and much more!
name: Volume 1

description:
"STEALING HOME"
A young ambitious runaway encounters a travelling salesman with sharp teeth and a hunger for the innocent.

SCOTT SNYDER (American Vampire, Batman, Swamp Thing), SCOTT TUFT and ATTILA FUTAKI (Percy Jackson) are back with 2011's most terrifying horror series. SEVERED.
name: Part Four: Stealing Home

description: Brubaker and McNiven continue their heart-stopping run on Cap with a nightmarish trip down memory lane - and that's bad news when your memory lane goes right through World War 2!
name: American Dreamers Part 4

description: When finally the forces of Emora and Songoria meet in open battle, who lives and who dies? Can Queen Sonja stop the Emperor's onslaught on Songoria from a hundred Leagues away? And once she sits on the Emperor's throne, will she ever give it up?

In recent years, more and more girls are experiencing the development of "tertiary sexual characteristics" during the later years of their puberty -- that is, the rapid masculinization of a certain part of their external genitalia. Ooi Haruka is one such girl, who has until now kept the changes in her body a secret from everyone but her family. However, after an embarassing incident involving the guy she's been crushing on in a crowded train, she wakes up to discover herself at school, surrounded by a group of students calling themselves the "Bra Girls (Swing Girls)." And they know her secret!?

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1: I Have a D…?
  • Chapter 2: I Made Friends with D… Girls!?
  • Chapter 3: I Need Men's Underwear…?
  • Chapter 4: I Send My Wishes…to the Stars?
  • Chapter 5: Show Me…So It Doesn't Show?
  • Chapter 6: I'll Show You…A Power-Up?
  • Chapter 7: It's A Camp Out…at the Beach?
  • Chapter 8: I'll Muster Up…All My Courage?
name: Ah! Pretty & Cheerful! They Are SWING GIRLS!

description: Zorro faces a crippling loss! Can he muster enough strength to do what he does best and fight back? The one and only Matt Wagner (MAGE, GRENDEL) is nearing the conclusion to his epic story of Zorro! Find out as Zorro Rides Again in issue #5!

Duke and Snake Eyes have arrived in Albania, bringing Rodrigo Vargas to the labs at Ray Pharm where the Madness Bug was created. Racing the clock to find the cure, Snake Eyes leads the charge as Duke slowly worsens… but Cobra won't give up the antidote without a fight!
name: Cobra Civil War Part 20

description: A G.I. JOE team led by FLINT has embarked on a dangerous operation and succeeded… but at what cost? With one of the Joes in critical condition, as well as the captured DARKLON in an injured state, desperate measures must be taken to ensure no casualties. Meanwhile, SNAKE EYES, STORM SHADOW and BILLY face the largest threat to the Arashikage clan yet! It's tough decisions and tougher Joes in this issue of G.I. Joe: A Real American Hero!

volume.name: G.I. Joe: A Real American Hero

description:
"ORIGIN," Part one of two

Creator HOANG NGUYEN presents an anthology of short stories set in the universe of the Carbon Grey. A boy becomes a god, two fictional characters come to life, a refugee becomes a queen and two sisters become killers. Legends, secret histories, and continuity errors " all will be revealed in CARBON GREY ORIGINS.
name: Origin, Part One

description: Hugo Strange and his Tyger soldiers use increasing desperate and dangerous means to try and capture Batman--even at the risk of harming innocent bystanders! As Batman and Commissioner Gordon hash over this latest eruption of violence, it becomes clear that Strange will take down anyone who tries to stand in his way. The only question is--who will be next?
name: Observations (Part 2)

description: Tony Stark squares off against Odin! And before it's all over, Tony's darkest secret is leaked to the world!
name: Iron Man

description: The Vulture returns! As the costs of Spider-Island continue to rise, Spidey's first enemy returns! High-rise robberies and teenaged jumpers force Spidey into a high flying new adventure...with a less than friendly partner.
name: Great Heights, Part One: Trust Issues

description: Libyan Desert, the sixth century. The Persian and Byzantine armies are at the gates of the capital of the small kingdom of N'Nas Amon. Surrounded on all sides, the queen decides to appeal to combat mercenaries, Sarmatians, to protect the young prince heir and take him to the city wren Jabbaren. But this will require breaking through the enemy lines...
name: Sept femmes engagées pour sauver l'héritier du royaume

description: In 6th century Libya, the capitol of an ancient nation is surrounded by the Persian and Byzantine armies. Seven are chosen to save the heir to the kingdom. Seven Warriors. Seven… sexy, gorgeous women? An exquisitely rendered tale in the vein of 300.
name: 1 of 3

description: 1941. Joshua Goldschmidt has developed a plan to end the war: 7 hiring men to assassinate Hitler and choose among these 7 killer called psychopaths or insane, the only ones capable of reasoning out standards and whose actions will not anticipated by the enemy. Churchill had agreed, they are parachuted over Germany ...
name: GN

description: Ireland, the ninth century. Seven monks living in community long ago turned their backs on the sacred principles of the Church. Everyone indulges body and soul to his sin of choice: that of pride, that envy, which in lust ... But the wrath of the Most High will descend on the capital in September sinners, as a dangerous mission: to evangelize the sea and fierce Vikings!
name: GN

description: 2093. Come in contact with artificial intelligence, men are on the verge of another step towards infinity. They will finally reach the gates of knowledge and the cosmos ... the only condition set by the Brothers of the Stars, to be united and at peace behind a single President. Utopia seems at hand. This is without counting the awakening of seven clones, programmed to kill the first leader of mankind.
name: GN

description: Paris, 1673, Molière died. At his funeral, Agnes was invited by Alceste, Argan and Scapin to join a group funded by Scrooge to discover who poisoned the illustrious author. Agnes is the depositary of the secret that can revive Don Juan, the only one to reveal the name of the seventh character, who, according to legend, will shed light on the truth.
name: GN

description: Jim Hawkins, the young hero of Treasure Island, became a trader, but only to pay the debts accumulating. His life is suddenly shattered by a summons to a mysterious rendezvous, where he stupor to find his former companions of fortune. They then announced that a sponsor wants them to anonymously return the island to retrieve the second part of Flint's treasure on Pirate ...
name: GN

description: 2062. On the moon, become a prison space which no one returns, the condemned discover a prehistoric cave. A mystery that intrigues as the wealthy French Laroche Galouseau he decided to mount an expedition. The problem is that to be sent there, it is killing ... Never mind, the flamboyant billionaire is willing to do anything to achieve his ends, even to take with him "six volunteers nominated!"
name: GN

description: French Alps. Confused by a snow shower, a car enters a tunnel. On board, a prey to some tension, a neurologist deemed his wife and brother. Not far behind, an Inspector of Narcotics, launched in pursuit of a pair of dangerous criminals ... Without knowing it, all are heading into a trap from hell, which will lead to their worst nightmares.
name: GN

description: Two thieves without scale, surviving as best they can of their thefts, are addressed by two dwarfs. They wish to use their talents as part of a risky mission, but very lucrative: seize the fabulous treasure of their people. To carry out this expedition, they need the two men but also a giant capable of carrying the loot and two ferocious orcs ...!
name: GN

description: Tokyo today. Kotobuki Ichiro, 92, leader of a yakuza clan feared and respected, is the subject of an attempted murder at the big party. The old man must sacrifice that saves the lives of his bodyguards and his astonishing vivacity. Collected by an old friend, Ichiro prepares a vengeance in which six men will lead to a terrible dance of death and blood ...
name: GN

description: An Elseworld where Catwoman is the Guardian of Gotham and Batman is a deranged killer.
name: Catwoman - Guardian of Gotham

volume.name: DC Comics Presents: Catwoman - Guardian of Gotham

description: REGENESIS TIE-IN! NEW CREATIVE TEAM! Hope and what is left of her five lights travel to China to find their latest recruit. Wait, is that X-Villain SEBASTIAN SHAW? James Asmus and Ibraim Roberson take the reins of the most-talked about new X-Book.

The New Mutants get back to their unfinished business! Tracking the mutant Blink, the team discovers her always near natural disaster areas. Is Blink somehow responsible for this destruction or is there something more sinister afoot? Part 1 of 3.
name: Blink and You Miss Her

description: In the nineteenth century in the forests of the moor of Dartmoor Scrubby is a child of the fairies who was switched at birth against a small human. He received a wonderful gift for an inheritance. However, it is soon forced to leave the forest for London.
name: The Maverick

description: WILL THE THUNDERBOLTS ONCE AGAIN FALL UNDER THE POWER OF ZEMO? Captain America and Namor have fallen before an army lead by the corrupted Human Torch. Now the only chance to keep the forces of the Red Skull from tipping the balance of war is The Thunderbolts! But for the Bolts to exist in the future, Zemo must not fall- will they switch sides once more? Jeff Parker and Kev Walker bring you the conclusion of the GOLDEN AGE THUNDERBOLTS!
name: The Fiery Death From Above

description: In the hope of a better life, Johnson settled in London. Despite this hostile environment, Scrubby manages to keep in touch with the marvelous.In the hope of a better life, Johnson settled in London. Despite this hostile environment, Scrubby manages to keep in touch with the marvelous.
name: The Boogeyman

description: The palm trees, deep in the forests, in every stone in the fields and plains ... Everywhere the spirit of nature is alive. Legend has it that every hundred years, a young boy to his parents will be removed by the fairies and that he will return transformed. He can now communicate with nature and its magical powers. It is said that the boy will fight the evil beings dedicated to the Lord of Chaos. It is said that his fight will depend on the future of the beings of Light. And this is the night when a star of infinite come crumbling amid a circle of stones that will begin the search for Changeling.
name: Edges of the Shadows

description: The mine collapsed, leaving the few survivors of that life protected by the common people. After the fire, Scrubby has now stood the test of the earth. The next she will be that of water? Everything leads us to think. Indeed, Laura, a friend of Scrubby, has been murdered near a strange tavern on the banks of the Thames ... Pierre Dubois invites us once again in the London of Jack the Ripper and Peter Pan. This 19th-century London with Xavier Fourquemin we exhale the mysteries and miseries of his line like no other.
name: Spring Heeled Jack

description: The undead of the “walking starvation” lurch into Camelot in the opening pages of Knights of the Living Dead by illustrator Dusty Higgins and writer Ron Wolfe. The mournful king, Arthur, has sentenced Queen Guinievere to burn for her infidelity, but he none-too-secretly expects her lover, Sir Lancelot, to save her. And here comes rescuer — Lancelot! — the greatest knight, on the greatest stallion. With a horde of the shambling dead behind him ...

AN ALL NEW STORY STARTS HERE! An offer to join Wolverine collides with an offer from the FF and X-23 is forced to decide if she wants to continue her life as an assassin or take a break and see what it’s like to be a regular teenager.
name: Misadventures in Babysitting, Part 1

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: The supernatural relic known as the Buddha's Tooth has been stolen, and the prime suspect is none other than Thomas Fleet AKA The Intrepid EscapeGoat! Pursued by the police and targeted by an unknown evil entity, EscapeGoat delves deeper into the mystery surrounding the object. Will the world's greatest escape artist survive the curse of the Buddha's Tooth, or will it be curtains for our intrepid hero? Don't miss this next exciting issue!"
name: 2 of 3

volume.name: The Intrepid Escape Goat: The Curse of the Buddha's Tooth

description:
In this new SCALPED collection featuring issues #43-49, Red Crow takes on a new challenger for tribal leadership, Dash pursues his mother's murderer, and Officer Falls Down faces a most unusual captivity.

Back Blurb

For a sheriff whose false front hides the emptiness inside, it means becoming the man he's always pretended to be.

For a bitter and bloody-handed FBI agent, it means risking it all to go down in a blaze of glory and a hail of bullets.

For the chief who's done his people wrong, it means confronting the father figure who wanted him to do right.

For an honest cop who's scarred but unspoiled, it means seeing if the goodness in his heart can survive when that heart is broken.

For a secret murderer who's half shaman, half madman, it means choosing whether to confess his crime directly to his executioner.

And for an undercover agent who no longer knows whose side he's on, it means choosing between saving a life... and taking one.
name: Vol. 8

volume.name: Scalped: You Gotta Sin to Get Saved

description:
Sin, Crossbones, and Valkeryie race across the globe in search the missing hammers!

The Secret Avengers guest-star in a battle against Raizo and an army of zombies!
name: Angels & Demons!

description: Norman Osborn and H.A.M.M.E.R. return! Witness the new Avengers line-up in action!
name: Avengers Assemble!

description: Colonel Mallory finds our hero rotting in solitary confinement, at his lowest ebb after the dreadful events of last issue. An offer of employment may provide respite but will taking a job like this one mean slamming the door forever on any hope of redemption?
name: 5: Here Comes a Candle to Light You to Bed

description: The Boys Volume 9 collects three separate story arcs, including the momentous issue #50, with bonus pin-ups and more! In issues #48-51: "Proper Preparation and Planning" - With Hughie absent, Butcher re-examines the Boys' first encounter with the Seven, trying to figure out what went wrong. But first there's some disquiet in the ranks to be dealt with, not to mention the return of an old and unexpected enemy who finally, incredibly, has come into his own. Meanwhile, on the Seven's floating headquarters, a flying lesson goes badly awry... In issues #52-55: "Barbary Coast" - Hughie travels out west to finally meet Lieutenant-Colonel Greg Mallory, the man who started The Boys. All kinds of secrets await our hero, beginning with the terrible story of the first supes to see action in World War Two. When the revelations cease, will Hughie return, or walk away from the team forever? In issues #56-59: "The Big Ride" - The countdown to the end begins, as Jack from Jupiter takes one step beyond... or does he? Hughie's triumphant return is not all he'd hoped for, but Butcher has bigger fish to fry. And The Boys meet the mysterious Doctor Peculiar...
name: Vol. 9

description: From the sparking-mad mind of Warren Ellis, the creator of TRANSMETROPOLITAN and PLANETARY, comes an electrical romance of a pirate utopia thwarted! In the London of 1830, newly-minted copper Charlie Gravel keeps seeing things he's not supposed to: a crooked Bow Street Runner with a flintlock revolver, high-flying vessels that are not supposed to fly, and the violent Scientific Phantasmagoria popularly known as Spring-Heeled Jack. With the coming of Captain Swing and his Electrical Pirates, history shall never be the same! This crackling new graphic novel is illustrated by Raulo Caceres in a stunning woodcut style, capturing the classic literary feel from days of yore. Available in softcover and hardcover formats, with illustrated covers by Raulo Caceres.
name: HC/TPB

volume.name: Captain Swing and the Electrical Pirates of Cindery Island

description:
New students! New staff! New West Coast Academy!

A Classic Avenger is murdered…and everyone’s a suspect!

Captain America, Luke Cage, and Hawkeye guest-star to…fight the Avengers Academy?
name: Disappointments

description:
Ride, Monsters, Ride! Humans are being killed in a wave of monster attacks...but the monsters are innocent! With a mystery murderer on the loose, and the survival of humanity at stake, Elsa Bloodstone and her sworn enemies the Legion of Monsters team up and hit the road!

Waves of monster attacks are happening all over, but all the monsters are being controlled by something bigger. It's up to Elsa Bloodstone and her sworn enemies, the Legion of Monsters, to team up and find out whats really going on.
name: RIDE, MONSTERS, RIDE!

description: Boundless Comics proudly collects, for the first time ever, the complete origin of fan-favorite comics heroine, Lady Death! In this second volume, a young woman once named Hope – who recently renounced her humanity to become a cold yet alluring warrior – pursues the evil warlock Sagos in an attempt to free her mother’s kidnapped soul. Allying herself with the mysterious duo, Wargoth and Satasha, she begins to understand the dark powers she wields… but will it be enough to face her enemy’s very skilled and very deadly lieutenants? LADY DEATH ORIGINS VOL. 2 collects the all five issues of “Blacklands” and three issues of “Sacrilege” story arcs in their entirety, as written by original creator Brian Pulido. Available in softcover format with illustrated cover by Rafa Lopez, a Hardcover by Juan Jose Ryp that is limited to 2500 copies, and a special Signed Hardcover with a new cover from Richard Ortiz and featuring a signature plate from creator and writer of Lady Death, Brian Pulido that is limited to 1000 copies!.
name: Vol. 2

description:
The creator of the acclaimed series TRANSMETROPOLITAN, Warren Ellis delivers PLANETARY, hailed as a timeless story that turned modern superhero conventions on their heads.

This graphic novel features the adventures of Elijah Snow, a hundred-year-old man, Jakita Wagner, an extremely powerful woman, and The Drummer, a man with the ability to communicate with machines. Tasked with tracking down evidence of super-human activity, these mystery archaeologists uncover unknown paranormal secrets and histories, such as a World War II supercomputer that can access other universes, a ghostly spirit of vengeance, and a lost island of dying monsters.

Introduction done by Alan Moore.
name: Book 1

volume.name: Planetary: All Over the World and Other Stories

description:
Get ready for the third hardcover collection of the acclaimed WildStorm series by Warren Ellis and John Cassaday! This stunning volume collects PLANETARY #13-18, featuring the continuing adventures of Elijah Snow, Jakita Wagner and the Drummer — the Archaelogists of the Unknown — as they piece together the mysteries of the world and begin a direct campaign against the four people hoarding Earth's unnatural secrets for themselves!

In this volume, Snow initiates the second part of his comeback plan to stop The Four, makes a startling revelation about his past, and uncovers information on the world's first moon shot...in 1851! As more and more secrets crumble, more and more new mysteries rise to take their place!
name: Book 3

description: This second PLANETARY collection focuses on the team's mysterious benefactor, the "Fourth Man." After paying their final respects to a British occultist with ties to their group, Elijah Snow, Jakita Wagner, and The Drummer continue their super-human archeological studies as they visit a hidden government compound full of radioactive human guinea pigs, discover a fictional construct that has been made real and learn of a malevolent group known simply as "The Four." As these investigations take place, Elijah begins to learn some truths about both the Fourth Man's identity as well as his own hidden past. Featuring an introduction by Buffy The Vampire Slayer creator, Joss Whedon!
name: Book 2

description: This is it – the final, spectacular hardcover collection of Warren Ellis and John Cassaday's PLANETARY. Collecting issues #19-27 of this unique series, Volume 4 features the final battles waged by Elijah Snow, Jakita Wagner and The Drummer against the mysterious Four along with the surprise return of a key player no one could have foreseen! It's been over a decade in the making – don't miss this unforgettable conclusion to one of WildStorm's most acclaimed series.
name: Book 4

description: Boundless unleashes our second on-going monthly series, written by Mike (Lady Death) Wolfer and featuring a whole new World that is populated by re-imagined versions of some of the most popular indy characters! Tensions are running high as the goddess Pandora and bayou swamp witch Anathema begin to unravel the mystery surrounding the horrific creatures which have invaded our dimension, but the enemy threat is about to reveal itself to be far worse than anyone could have imagined. A dark force from a parallel universe has possessed an innocent woman, transforming her into the fire-wielding Hellina and with the brain-washed and blood-thirsty Widow at her side, she has unleashed a reign of terror within one of Pandora’s prime business holdings, right in the heart of downtown Miami. With so many innocent lives on the line, Pandora’s options are narrowing to either hoping for some miraculous solution or killing every last person in the Promethea Building… Including her possessed allies! This epic saga is written by Mike (Lady Death) Wolfer and featured the art of Pow Rodrix wrapped in a stunning new cover by Matt Martin! Available with a Regular or Gore cover by Matt Martin, as well as a Wraparound and a special Art Nouveau Retailer Order Incentive by painter Michael Dipascale!

FINAL ISSUE! Stan Lee, SUPERMAN’S Chris Roberson, and SPIDER-MAN’s Khary Randolph bring the sci-fi superhero scorcher to a close in this can’t-miss epic conclusion to the crossover that has everyone talking. With alien superpowers threatening Earth with annihilation, Starborn must step up, alongside Soldier Zero and the Traveler, to save civilization -- but which civilization will Starborn fight for? Find out in Stan Lee’s grand finale that will change the way you read comics forever!
